
[1]diallage

   DIALLAGE, n. [Gr., difference, alluding to the difference of luster
   between its natural joints.] A mineral, the smaragdite of Saussure, of
   a lamellar or foliated structure. Its subspecies are green diallage,
   metalloidal diallage and bronzite. The metalloidal subspecies is called
   schillersteing, or shiller spar.
